            <section class="prose">
              <h2>How this currency converter works</h2>
              <p>
                This tool uses live mid-market exchange rates (the “real” rate
                between banks) as the baseline. You can then optionally add your
                bank’s fee or spread to see the effective rate you’ll actually
                get.
              </p>

              <h3>Conversion formula</h3>
              <div class="formula-box text-sm">
                <p><strong>1. Base conversion (no fee):</strong></p>
                <p>Converted amount = Amount × Rate<sub>from→to</sub></p>
                <p class="mt-2">
                  <strong>2. With fee deducted from result:</strong>
                </p>
                <p>Net amount = Converted amount × (1 − fee%)</p>
                <p class="mt-2">
                  <strong>3. With rate markup (worse rate):</strong>
                </p>
                <p>Effective rate = Rate<sub>from→to</sub> × (1 − fee%)</p>
                <p>Net amount = Amount × Effective rate</p>
              </div>

              <h3>Mid-market vs. bank rates</h3>
              <p>
                The mid-market rate is the midpoint between the buy and sell
                prices on the global FX market. Banks and card networks usually
                add a spread (for example 2–4%) plus possible fixed fees. By
                entering your estimated fee percentage, you can compare:
              </p>
              <ul>
                <li>
                  <strong>Mid-market amount</strong> – ideal benchmark with no
                  fees.
                </li>
                <li>
                  <strong>Net amount</strong> – what you actually receive after
                  fees.
                </li>
                <li>
                  <strong>Effective rate</strong> – the real rate implied by
                  your bank’s charges.
                </li>
              </ul>

              <h2>Tips for using the converter</h2>
              <ul>
                <li>
                  Use the <strong>Swap</strong> button to quickly reverse the
                  conversion direction.
                </li>
                <li>
                  Check the <strong>Quick conversions</strong> row to see how
                  your base currency compares to several popular currencies at
                  once.
                </li>
                <li>
                  Look at the <strong>30‑day history</strong> to see if today’s
                  rate is relatively high or low before exchanging a large
                  amount.
                </li>
              </ul>

              <h3>Limitations & data source</h3>
              <p>
                Rates are for informational purposes only and may be delayed by
                a short interval. They are not a quote or guarantee from any
                financial institution. Always confirm the final rate and fees
                with your bank, broker, or card issuer before making a
                transaction.
              </p>
            </section>

